description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has come up within South Central Ambulance Service (SCAS) as a Team Leader for our Patient Transport Service (PTS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Patient Transport Service is a pivotal role within SCAS, providing a safe and efficient transport of patients to and from healthcare settings and their home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Team Leader you will be responsible for the day to day supervision and management of a team of Ambulance Care Assistants (ACA’s) that work on the Patient Transport Service. This will involve the management of personnel, monitoring performance management, sickness and annual leave following relevant HR Policies and Procedures. You will be familiar with and adhere to service plans policies, procedures and Key Performance Indicators (KPI’s)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition you will need to resolve any localised fleet issues and maintain stations in prepared readiness and for auditing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will provide leadership and management direction to the operational teams at our High Wycombe, Amersham and Chalfont PTS stations. You will work closely with the Senior Operations Manager to ensure that service delivery maintains the standards required as per our contractual arrangements and Service Level Agreements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be an ambassador for the Trust, and in particular PTS, assisting in the development of close working relationships with our users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will possess:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent listening skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Problem solving and decision-making skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage and lead a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritise own workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What SCAS will give you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automatic enrolment to the NHS Pension Scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Starting annual leave entitlement of 27 days plus bank holidays, rising to 33 days after 10 years’ service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for career development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to apply for continuing professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to apply for other educational qualifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occupational Health support along with an Employee Assistance Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see the job description and person specification for further details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please state in your supporting statement how you meet the criteria outlined in the attached person specification.&lt;/p&gt;
